\section{Evaluation}

\subsection{Test Results}

Comprehensive testing was conducted across all language components. Table~\ref{tab:tests} presents the real test results from the project's test suite.

\begin{table}[h]
\centering
\caption{Unit Test Results}
\label{tab:tests}
\begin{tabular}{@{}lcccc@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{Test Category} & \textbf{Total} & \textbf{Passed} & \textbf{Failed} & \textbf{Pass Rate} \\
\midrule
Lexer Tests & 33 & 33 & 0 & 100\% \\
Parser Tests & 68 & 68 & 0 & 100\% \\
Interpreter Tests & 215 & 215 & 0 & 100\% \\
Corpus Tests & 2 & 2 & 0 & 100\% \\
Golden Tests & 2 & 2 & 0 & 100\% \\
CLI Smoke Tests & 3 & 3 & 0 & 100\% \\
CLI Flags Tests & 18 & 16 & 2 & 88.9\% \\
Bytecode Tests & 2 & 2 & 0 & 100\% \\
\midrule
\textbf{Total} & \textbf{343} & \textbf{341} & \textbf{2} & \textbf{99.4\%} \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

The 2 failed tests relate to the package manager feature, which is still under development. All core language functionality tests pass successfully.

\subsection{Performance Benchmarks}

Table~\ref{tab:performance} presents real performance benchmarks from the JIT compiler test suite.

\begin{table}[h]
\centering
\caption{Performance Benchmark Results}
\label{tab:performance}
\begin{tabular}{@{}llll@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{Benchmark} & \textbf{Iterations} & \textbf{Time} & \textbf{Ops/sec} \\
\midrule
Arithmetic Operations & 100,000 & 27ms & 3.6M \\
Loop Iterations & 10,000 & 1.4ms & 7.0M \\
Fibonacci (recursive) & 50,000 & 8.5ms & 5.9M \\
Matrix Multiplication & 50,000 & 51ms & 981K \\
Recursion Simulation & 100,000 & 32ms & 3.1M \\
Text Processing & 100,000 & 13ms & 7.8M \\
Stress Test & 1,000 & 50ms & 19.9M \\
Tiered Compilation & 10,000 & 18ms & 555K \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\textbf{Overall JIT Speedup: 5.08x} compared to baseline interpretation.

\subsection{Component Performance}

Table~\ref{tab:components} shows performance of individual compiler components.

\begin{table}[h]
\centering
\caption{Component Performance Metrics}
\label{tab:components}
\begin{tabular}{@{}lll@{}}
\toprule
\textbf{Component} & \textbf{Technology} & \textbf{Performance} \\
\midrule
Lexer & Rust NFA & $<1$ms per 1000 lines \\
Parser & Recursive Descent & $<5$ms per 1000 lines \\
Interpreter & Tree-Walking & $\sim$33ms per 1000 iterations \\
Bytecode VM & Stack-based & 0.49 instructions/$\mu$s \\
JIT Compiler & 5-Tier & 5.08x speedup \\
\bottomrule
\end{tabular}
\end{table}

\subsection{Usability Considerations}

While a formal usability study is planned for future work, preliminary feedback from early adopters indicates:

\begin{itemize}
    \item Arabic keywords reduce cognitive load for native Arabic speakers
    \item Vibe Coding significantly lowers the barrier to entry
    \item RTL support in editor integrations improves developer experience
    \item Arabic error messages are more accessible than English alternatives
\end{itemize}

