\section{Applications and Use Cases}

\subsection{Educational Applications}

Al-Marjaa is particularly suited for computer science education in Arabic-speaking regions. The language enables students to:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Focus on algorithmic thinking without English syntax overhead
    \item Learn programming concepts in their native language
    \item Transition to mainstream languages with reduced cognitive burden
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Enterprise Development}

The performance characteristics make Al-Marjaa suitable for production applications:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Business applications with Arabic interfaces
    \item AI-powered systems using ONNX integration
    \item Cross-platform applications with UI framework
\end{itemize}

\subsection{AI-Powered Arabic Applications}

The combination of native AI support and Arabic syntax enables:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Arabic chatbots and conversational AI
    \item Arabic text analysis and sentiment analysis
    \item Arabic speech recognition applications
    \item Machine translation systems
\end{itemize}

% ============================================================
% القسم 7: حدود الدراسة
% ============================================================
\section{Limitations}

This work has several limitations that should be acknowledged:

\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Formal Usability Study:} The current evaluation lacks a controlled user study with statistical analysis. While preliminary feedback is positive, rigorous empirical validation is needed.
    
    \item \textbf{Ecosystem Maturity:} The language has a limited package ecosystem compared to established languages. The package manager feature is still under development (evidenced by 2 failing tests).
    
    \item \textbf{Platform Support:} Current implementation focuses on desktop platforms. Mobile development SDK is planned but not yet available.
    
    \item \textbf{IDE Integration:} While VS Code extension exists, support for other IDEs is limited.
    
    \item \textbf{Vibe Coding Accuracy:} Complex program generation requires refinement; the system achieves 94\% accuracy for simple tasks but only 67\% for complex ones.
\end{enumerate}

